benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: POST /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/tags - Add tags to account

covered: Valid Payload: Multiple scenarios (TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04, TC05, TC18, TC19) cover successful addition of tags with valid data.

Invalid Payload: Tests for empty body (TC07), malformed body (TC08), extra parameters (TC17), large payloads (TC18), duplicate IDs (TC19), and injection attempts (TC22) cover validation and malformed data handling.
Edge Cases: Scenarios for no existing tags (TC04), existing tags (TC05), and large number of tags (TC18) are included.
Error Handling: Tests for non-existent account (TC14), invalid accountId format (TC13), missing accountId (TC12), and account not found are present.
Authorization: Test for missing header (TC11), missing token (implied in scenario), and unauthorized access (TC15) are included.
Special Characters & Regression: Tests for special characters in IDs (TC23) and previous issues (TC23) are covered.
Concurrency & Performance: Scenarios for concurrent requests (TC21) and performance timing (TC20) are included.
gaps: Rate Limiting: No tests cover system behavior under high request volume or throttling.
Caching Behavior: No scenarios test caching headers like ETag or Cache-Control.
Pagination & Sorting: While TC06 mentions ignoring parameters, no dedicated tests verify pagination, sorting, or filtering behavior.
Security & Injection: No explicit tests for injection in headers or request body beyond basic validation.
Response Content Validation: While response status and basic body content are checked, detailed validation of the returned Tag objects is limited.
recommendations: Add explicit tests for rate limiting and throttling to ensure system stability under load.
Include tests verifying caching headers and cache invalidation behavior.
Create dedicated pagination, sorting, and filtering tests to confirm parameters are ignored or handled correctly.
Implement security tests for injection attempts in headers and request bodies.
Enhance response validation to verify the structure and content of returned Tag objects in detail.
